-- RioZim to Pay Centametall Debt Over 66 Months, Newsday Reports
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-08-20T09:04:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-20/riozim-to-pay-centametall-debt-over-66-months-newsday-reports.html
RioZim Ltd. (RIOTZ)  will pay an outstanding
$6.6 million debt to Centametall AG over 66 months,  Newsday
reported , citing RioZim Managing Director Ashton Ndlovu.  The settlement accord for the ending of a toll-refining
contract involved $13.6 million due to Centametall and RioZim
taking over the Empress nickel refinery, which has a potential
value of $58 million, Harare-based Newsday said on its  website .
The company has delivered $7 million of metal to Centametall as
part of the settlement, it said. The repayment of the $6.6
million balance will begin in April 2014, it said.  RioZim, which also mines gold, produced 62 kilograms (137
pounds) of the metal in the second quarter of this year,
compared with 55 kilograms in the previous three months, Newsday
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
